# Entity service colors (user + admin portals)

Entity identity on portal content — **not** status pills, route chips, or primary buttons.

## Source of truth

| Piece | Path |
|-------|------|
| Base hues + derived tokens | `src/styles/_entity-service-accent.scss` (imported in `styles.scss`) |
| Type | `shared/constants/entity-context-class.ts` → `entityContextClass(tab)` |
| User | `entity-context--{transport\|freight\|warehouse}` — `UserEntityTab` in `user-urls.ts` |
| Admin | `entity-context--{users\|vehicles\|warehouses}` — `AdminEntityTab` in `admin-urls.ts` |

**Current bases** (change only in `_entity-service-accent.scss`):

| Service | Light | Dark |
|---------|-------|------|
| Transport | `#0077d4` (blue) | `#38bdf8` |
| Freight | `#e85d04` (orange) | `#fb923c` |
| Warehouse | `#9333ea` (purple) | `#e879f9` |
| Admin users | `#059669` (emerald) | `#34d399` |
| Admin vehicles | `#0077d4` (same as transport) | `#38bdf8` |
| Admin warehouses | `#9333ea` (same as warehouse) | `#e879f9` |

Admin **users** uses **emerald** (not blue/teal) so it stays distinct from vehicles (blue) and warehouses (purple), and does not read as error red.

## Chrome intensity

Default `entity-context-tokens` mixin — **signal** level on user entities + admin vehicles/warehouses:

- Border + icon: full base hue (`--entity-accent`)
- Active tab fill: 18% base tint
- Table spine: 70% base; hover spine: full base

**Exception:** `.entity-context--users` overrides to **softer** mixes (60% border, 85% icon, 50%/75% spine) — still emerald hue, less aggressive than signal chrome.

## Do not use for

- `StatusBadgeComponent` / `--status-*` (workflow only — `open` = green, `canceled` = red; see `entity-status.mdc`)
- Route chips (`--chip-neutral-*`)
- `--portal-accent` (guest login / portal picker only)
- Full card backgrounds or primary CTAs

## UX pattern — “accent spine”

| State | Entity cards (tables, primary form/detail surface) |
|-------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| Rest | **3px left** + **1px top** `--entity-accent-spine`; other sides `1px` neutral |

| State | Entity create menu options, active entity tabs |
|-------|-----------------------------------------------|
| Rest | **3px left spine** + **colored icon** (`--entity-accent-icon`) |
| Hover / focus | Stronger spine, `--entity-accent-border`, `--entity-accent-hover-bg`, shadow |

Icons + labels remain required (color-blind safe).

## SCSS mixins (`_entity-service-accent.scss`)

| Mixin | Effect |
|-------|--------|
| `entity-card-accent-rest` | **3px left** + **1px top** `--entity-accent-spine`; other sides `1px` neutral |
| `entity-card-accent-spine` | **3px left** only — stacks below a surface that has the top cap |

**Connected stack (forms + details):** first card gets `entity-card-accent-rest`; cards below get `entity-card-accent-spine` so the left spine continues from the top cap. Hub table cards each get full `entity-card-accent-rest` (controls + data are separate units, not a vertical stack).

| Component | Input | When to set |
|-----------|-------|-------------|
| `PageTitleComponent` | `entityTab` | User + admin entity create/edit + detail pages |
| `FormPageComponent` | `entityTab` | User + admin entity create/edit — top cap on stepper or first section; left spine on following sections |
| `DetailPageLayoutComponent` | `entityTab` | User + admin entity detail — top cap on summary; left spine on detail cards below |
| `DataTableComponent` | `entityTab`, `tableChromeVariant?` | User hub tables + admin hub tables: set `entityTab`. Chrome layout: default `'splitCard'`; legacy `'bandLadder'` |
| `EntityTabsComponent` | `accentMode` | User + admin hubs: default `'entity'` — active pill gets `entity-context--{tab}`. Use `'neutral'` only when tabs must stay uncolored |
| `EntityCreateMenuComponent` | per-option `entityTab` | Colored spine + icon on create dropdown options (user + admin) |

Apply class via `entityContextClass()` or host/`ngClass` — do not hardcode hex in component SCSS.

## Hub tables (`DataTableComponent`)

Default layout is **split card** (`tableChromeVariant` default `'splitCard'`): filters in `.data-table-controls-card`, table in `.data-table-data-card`. Entity chrome styles in `_entity-service-accent.scss` under `app-data-table.data-table--split-card`.

When `entityTab` is set on host:

- **Controls card (desktop + mobile):** `1px` neutral on right/bottom + **3px left** + **1px top** `--entity-accent-spine`; no filter-active border upgrade
- **Data card (desktop):** same spine as controls card
- **Data card (mobile ≤768px):** flat list shell — transparent, no border, no entity spine; canvas shows between row cards
- **Filter state:** communicated via chips band, active count (`--entity-accent-icon`), and mobile toggle dot — not card border hierarchy
- **Chips band:** neutral `--bg-table-filter-chips` only — no entity soft wash
- Row hover: `--entity-accent-row-hover`
- **Mobile row cards (≤768px) and desktop card view:** `entity-card-accent-rest` per row — entity spine on each item; stacked label-above-value fields with subtle dividers
- **Desktop list view:** data card keeps full entity spine; row cards N/A (HTML table)

**Do not** duplicate accent: split-card suppresses grey `border-left` on inner `.data-table-filters--active` — entity spine lives on the controls card only (`table-filters.mdc`). Neutral admin tables still use grey `3px` left on `.data-table-controls-card--active` when filtered.

Table entity chrome lives in `_entity-service-accent.scss` + `_table-chrome-split-card.scss` (global) to stay within component SCSS budget.

## Form + detail cards (`FormPageComponent`, `DetailPageLayoutComponent`)

Entity chrome in `_entity-service-accent.scss` — `entity-card-accent-rest`: `1px` neutral right/bottom + **3px left** + **1px top** `--entity-accent-spine`.

When `entityTab` is set on host:

**Form pages** (`app-form-page[class*='entity-context--']`):

- **First surface (left + top):** `.form-stepper-card` (stepper forms) or first `.form-section-card` in `.form-page__sections` (single-step)
- **Following surfaces (left spine only):** step section cards in `.form-page__step-content`, or `.form-section-card` after the first in single-step
- **Excluded:** `--flat` / `--headless` variants; guest register/login (no `entityTab`)

**Detail pages** (`app-detail-page-layout[class*='entity-context--']`):

- **First surface (left + top):** `.entity-detail-summary` glance band
- **Following surfaces (left spine only):** `.detail-page-card` (body, loading)
- **Excluded:** `DetailActionBarComponent`

Set the same `entityTab` on `PageTitleComponent` (icon tint), `FormPageComponent` / `DetailPageLayoutComponent` (card accent), and `DataTableComponent` (hub tables) on entity pages.

### Wiring checklist (new entity CRUD)

1. Hub table page: `[entityTab]="'<tab>'"` on `app-data-table`
2. Form page: `entityTab="<tab>"` on `app-page-title` **and** `app-form-page`
3. Detail page: `entityTab="<tab>"` on `app-page-title` **and** `app-detail-page-layout`
4. Guest register/login — omit `entityTab` on all of the above

1. Extend `UserEntityTab` + `USER_ENTITY_TABS` in `user-urls.ts`
2. Add bases + `.entity-context--*` block in `_entity-service-accent.scss`
3. Wire tabs, home config, table pages, icons in `user-page-icons.ts`

